    ('13', '27.7120863' ,'85.3155623','The Chimney Restaurant','All of our dining options have one thing in common, delicious food made from healthy, ingredients prepared by our devoted chefs. We proudly source regional and organic products and buy from speciality suppliers to bring our diners the healthiest, tastiest cuisine we can. Before or after your meal, our lively bar offers a wide array of cocktails, beers and wines to suit any thirst.','https://www.yakandyeti.com/templates/yootheme/cache/intro-chimney-c78f1a1a.jpeg','3','https://www.yakandyeti.com/templates/yootheme/cache/spice-room-intro-83ed1d6a.jpeg','https://www.yakandyeti.com/images/dining/chimney/chimney-outdoor-4.jpg '),
    ('14', '27.7024949','85.311008' ,'Bhojan Griha','The 150 year old heritage, Bhojan Griha was started to give an example to the government that old buildings need to be respected. The building was in a very dilapidated state and going to be demolished, so in 1998 Bharat Basnet took over the building previously resided by the Royal Priest of The King of Nepal and completely renovated it. The goal was to take locals and use traditional methods and materials to construct buildings to experience the feeling of the past whilst enjoying the music and food in Nepal. “What we eat is what we are” – we work with Chi philosophy to discourage chemical/commercial farming practices. We are constantly working with local producers to encourage traditional/organic way of farming.  Dine to experience Nepali cuisine in a 150 year old heritage building which housed the late Royal Priest of the King of Nepal. You will be served with food prepared from local organic sources from our very own farm. Elevate your senses with the folk dance and music of Nepal! ','https://www.bhojangriha.com/images/banners/bhojan-griha-kathmandu-building.jpg','3','https://www.bhojangriha.com/images/banners/bhojan-griha-kamasutra-bar-kathmandu-banner.jpg','https://www.bhojangriha.com/images/banners/bhojan-griha-kathmandu-nepali-cultural-program-banner.jpg'),
    ('15', '27.7024949','85.311008' ,'Mulchowk Restaurant','In the beautiful main courtyard (Mul Chowk in Nepali) of Babar Mahal Revisited, Mul Chowk provides to all a unique experience bringing culinary art closer to all other forms of culture.
    Whether a quiet lunch meeting, or celebrations we offer fine dining with a refined twist. Serving continental a la carte, elegant cocktails and lavish customized menus for your events, the Mul Chowks team is here to serve you on any occasion.
    THE CHOWK: In days gone by, Chowk (the main courtyard) in homes and places was centre of community activities. Mul Chowk restaurant, as a classic piece of architecture, aspires to bring back the cultural relevance of the Chowk.
    THE RESTAURANT: Shaded under the sanctified Rudraksha tree, the southern orientation of Mul Chowks courtyard ensures yearly sunshine and light, making it a perfect location for lunches and brunches.
    It holds musical concerts and performances of various kinds. When booked for events, Mul Chowk can accommodate up to 200 guests. The menus varies from Continental to Indian depending on your needs. The palace is also available for corporate functions with a complete boardroom set up. Mul Chowk provides lunch boxes and delivers food within Kathmandu. 
    ','https://pagevamp-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/users/395181273869074/f8815d3157f140b2bc748a337d3e881a.jpg','3','https://ktmguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/b5.jpg','https://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-s/03/af/f0/80/mulchowk-restaurant.jpg'),
    ('16', '27.7066867','85.3170543' ,'Medicare National Hospital & Research Center','Existing health service facilities in Nepal are still insufficient to meet the growing need of reliable health care. This is why a significant number of patients are going to different hospitals of neighboring countries like India and Thailand for treatment. Ultimately this causes drainage of huge amount of foreign exchange from Nepal and great inconvenience to patients and their relatives. Urgent need for establishment of well equipped and reliable health care centre of international standard has always been felt. ','','2','',''),
    ('17', '27.7066867','85.3170543','Grande City Hospital','Grande City Hospital (P) Ltd is a 24 beds world class health care facility at Jyoti Bhawan, Kantipath -right in the heart of the Kathmandu city. Initially established as Grande City Clinic & Diagnostic Service in 2013, the hospital provides quality health care with state-of-the-art and latest technologies combined with the expertise of highly qualified and trained doctors and professionals.
    The main purpose of the hospital is to provide world-class healthcare facilities in a compassionate environment with optimum utilization of modern technologies. ','https://ktmguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/5a801c5278950.jpg 
	','2','	https://assets-cdn.kathmandupost.com/uploads/source/news/2019/health/09302016_GRANDE_HOSPITAL__MG_7988.jpg ','	https://myrepublica.nagariknetwork.com/uploads/media/G_20200523155316.jpg'),
    ('18', '27.7066867','85.3170543' ,'Bir Hospital','Bir Hospital is the oldest hospital of Nepal. This hospital was established in 1947 BS, under the name of contemporary Prime Minister Bir Shamsher Jung Bahadur Rana. Initially it was a seven bed hospital with 5 staffs. Today it has a proud history of 125 years and the first hospital of Nepal wherethe practice of modern medicinecommenced.Till eighties services including gynaecology, paediatrics and psychiatry were available in this very hospital. With the evolvement of super specialtyand increasing workload in the limited premises these services were shifted to Indra Rajya Laxmi Devi Shah Maternity hospital Thapathali, Kanti Bal hospital Maharajgunja and Patan mental hospital Lalitpur respectively.
    This is a historical hospital as every modern medical service in the country has roots in this hospital. This is the first hospital where neurosurgery was started in the times when CTscan was not around. In the field of modern cardiology Nepal’s first case of angiography, cathlab and valve replacement were all done at Bir Hospital. Every senior doctor who was a pioneer in the field of modern medicine in Nepal like Dr. Mrigendra Raj Pandey, Dr. Anjani Kumar Sharma, Dr. Dinesh Nath Gongal, Dr. Shabitri Gurung, Dr. Dibyashree Malla, Dr Sudip Kumar Bhattacharya, Dr. Mohin Shah, Dr. Puskar Satyal, Dr. Ishor Lal Acharya, Dr. Dhrub Lal Singh, Dr. Dambar Bahadur Karki, Dr. Sachche Kumar Pahadi, Dr. Dharma Sharan Manadhar, Dr. Ram Prasad Pokharel, Dr. Yanta Mani Pradhan, Dr Ram Bhadra Adiga, Dr. LN Prasad, Dr. JP Rijal, Dr. Jwala Raj Pandey, Dr. Basant Lal Shrestha, Dr. Gopal Achary, Dr. Hemanga Dixit, Dr. Shankar Bahadur Shrestha, Dr. NB Amatya, Dr. Laxman Paudel hadstarted their careers in this hospital. These pioneers are the heroes and the legends of modern medicine in Nepal. Bir hospital is the central hospital where services were provided the royal family members in past.  
    ','https://nams.org.np/images/bir.jpg  ','2','https://assets-cdn.kathmandupost.com/uploads/source/news/2019/miscellaneous/Bir_Hospital-21112018065706-1000x0.jpg  ','https://i0.wp.com/www.peoplesreview.com.np/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/Bir-Hospital.jpg'),
    ('19', '27.7467476','85.3405063' ,'Shahid Gangalal National Heart Center','Shahid Gangalal National Heart Centre (SGNHC) is a hospital which provides cardiac care, diagnostic and treatment procedures in Kathmandu, Nepal.[1][2] The hospital is named after Gangalal Shrestha.[2] It is the first cardiac tertiary center in Nepal. 
    ','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/3f/Shahid_Gangalal_National_Heart_Centre1.jpg 
	','2','https://ktmguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/g2.jpg ','https://ktmguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/g7.jpg '),
	('20', '27.7467476','85.3405063' ,'Upendra Devkota Memorial National Institute Of Neurological And Allied Sciences','Upendra Devkota (18 December 1953 – 18 June 2018) was a Nepali neurosurgeon and founder of the first neurological trauma unit in Nepal, located at Bir Hospital. He held the post of Minister for Health, Science and Technology, Government of Nepal. Devkota was the founder of the National Institute of Neurological and Allied Sciences.
    He was born in Gorkha in 1953 and received his high school education in amar Jyoti Janata High School (commonly known as Luintel High School of Gorkha), Palungtar, Gorkha, Nepal. He was a classmate friend of Baburam Bhattarai from class eight to Isc.[1] He did intermediate of sciences (I Sc) education from Amrit Science college, Tribhuvan University, Kathmandu, Nepal and got Colombo Plan fellowship to pursue medical education in India. He completed Bachelor of medicine and bachelor of surgery (MBBS) in 1978 from Assam Medical College, Dibrugarh, Assam, India and worked some years in Bir Hospital under Dr DN Gongol. He had also been a Health Minister of then His Majesty government of Nepal.
    For advanced training in neurosurgery, he went to the United Kingdom, where he trained at Atkinson Morley Hospital (now part of St Georges Hospital), Southern General Hospital Glasgow. He returned to Nepal in 1989 and started Neurosurgery in Bir Hospital. He established NINAS in Bansbari, Kathmandu, Nepal.  ','
	https://myrepublica.nagariknetwork.com/uploads/media/2018/June/neuro-hospital.jpg ','2','https://neuro.org.np/userfiles/files/hospital.jpg ','https://i.ytimg.com/vi/aehvicqLUwU/maxresdefault.jpg'),
